 <li>For students, Ryerson’s&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/studentlearningsupport/academic-accommodation-support/">Academic Accommodation Support (AAS)</a>, currently considers requests for use of medical marijuana on a case-by-case basis, following practices and procedures informed by Senate<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/senate/policies/pol159.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>&nbsp;Policy 159<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span></a>.</li> 
 <li>For staff and faculty,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/hr/contact/workplace-wellbeing/">Workplace Wellbeing Services</a>&nbsp;continues to assess all medical marijuana workplace accommodation requests through standard process, and reviews all requests as per the <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/policies/policy-list/accommodation-disabilities-policy/">Accommodation for Persons with Disabilities Policy.</a></li> 
</ol> 
