                        <a id="accordion-1536264127697-how-will-misconduct-inappropriate-behaviour-related-to-the-use-of-alcohol-drugs-be-managed-on-campus--" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#d3fada3f-2f31-47fa-92b2-e23bd6a71368" href="#accordion-content-1536264127697-how-will-misconduct-inappropriate-behaviour-related-to-the-use-of-alcohol-drugs-be-managed-on-campus--" aria-controls="accordion-content-1536264127697-how-will-misconduct-inappropriate-behaviour-related-to-the-use-of-alcohol-drugs-be-managed-on-campus--" aria-expanded="false">
                            How will misconduct/inappropriate behaviour related to the use of alcohol/drugs be managed on campus? 
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1536264127697-how-will-misconduct-inappropriate-behaviour-related-to-the-use-of-alcohol-drugs-be-managed-on-campus--" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1536264127697-how-will-misconduct-inappropriate-behaviour-related-to-the-use-of-alcohol-drugs-be-managed-on-campus--">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1536264127697 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="f5d091ca-35e6-427d-8b10-6e01d460a376" >

    <p>Impact of misbehaviour on campus and in the workplace as a result of the &nbsp;use of controlled substances will be addressed as follows:</p> 
<p><strong>Students:</strong></p> 
<p>While current practices favour resolutions based on a harm reduction and educational approach, consequences for any inappropriate behaviour on campus related to the use of alcohol/drugs may be addressed through the<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/calendar/2018-2019/policies-and-procedures/rights-conduct/codes-of-conduct/"> Student Code of Non-Academic Conduct (Policy 61)</a>.</p> 
<p>As with all controlled legal substances, Ryerson students are expected to behave responsibly and to conduct themselves appropriately. </p> 
<p><strong>Employees:</strong></p> 
<p>Consuming recreational cannabis in the workplace is illegal, and continues to be after legalization. Employees are expected to continue to arrive to work unimpaired and fit to perform their duties.</p> 
<p>For faculty and staff, community members may work closely with their Human Resources consultant to follow standard practices and procedures as outlined in HR policy and collective agreements.</p>
    





</div>
